  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Can diabetic patients maintain their blood glucose in a normal range after receiving a corticosteroid injection?</measure>
    <time_frame>4 weeks</time_frame>
    <description>The main outcome variable in this study is to determine what effects, if any, a corticosteroid injection has on the ability of diabetic patients to maintain their blood glucose in a normal range. This will allow for better patient education when discussing the risks of corticosteroid injections and allow for improved post-injection care of patients.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <number_of_arms>2</number_of_arms>
  <enrollment type="Actual">0</enrollment>
